.TH "usb_ep_set_maxpacket_limit" 9 "usb_ep_set_maxpacket_limit" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
usb_ep_set_maxpacket_limit \- set maximum packet size limit for endpoint
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" usb_ep_set_maxpacket_limit
.BI "(struct usb_ep *ep "  ","
.BI "unsigned maxpacket_limit "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ep" 12
the endpoint being configured
.IP "maxpacket_limit" 12
value of maximum packet size limit
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function should be used only in UDC drivers to initialize endpoint
(usually in probe function).
